# Follow Notification Feature

## Context
The follow system works (toggle follow/unfollow in `interactService.js`), and `formatNoficationType.js` already maps `follow: 'Follows you'` — but the backend never actually creates a notification when someone follows a user. The notification card also has no icon or rendering branch for `follow` type. This change wires it all up end-to-end.

## Files to Modify

### 1. `server/services/interactService.js` (lines 395-410) — Create notification on follow
In the `addFollowsService` `else` branch (new follow), after the successful INSERT into `follows`, add a notification INSERT:

```js
// Only notify if not self-follow
if (followerId !== followingId) {
    await supabase
        .from('notifications')
        .insert({
            sender_id: followerId,
            receiver_id: followingId,
            type: 'follow',
            read: false
        });
}
```

- `journal_id` is omitted (null) — the notification query uses `journals!journal_id(...)` which returns null gracefully for missing FKs (same pattern as constellation notifications)
- No deduplication needed — matches the pattern of other notification types (likes, etc.)

